%Taha Zulfiqar, zulfiq11 1001476379

%======================SENTENCES (S)===================

S -> NP VP | NP_PPNoun VPItProp | NP_PPNoun VPTProp


%======================NOUN PHRASE (NP)===================

% adj phase (see below), (det AP), common nouns (the cat/cats), her brown cat/her cat
NP -> AP | DetP AP | DetP NComm | DetVow NSingVow

%Personal Pronouns(she/they), Proper Nouns (Nadia, Toronto)
NP_PPNoun -> NPersp | NPrp

%Common Nouns
NComm -> NSing | NPlural | NMass | NSingVow

%Includes proper noun
NP_AllObj -> NP | NPrp | PosProN

%Adj common noun (brown cat), brown cats, soft snow, soft wet snow/cat/cats
AP -> Adj NComm | Adj AP

%======================Deteminers (Det)===================
%Can be possessive pronouns or determiners 
DetP -> Det | PosProN

%======================PREPOSITION PHASE (PP)===================

%Standard prepositional phrase: (in, with, to NP)
PP -> P NP | P NPrp

%======================VERB PHRASE (VP)===================

VP -> VP_It | VP_T 

%======================VERB PHRASE Intransitive (VP_It)===================

%VP for intrasitivies that includes PP
VP_It -> VPItProp | PP VP_It

%Intransitive involving Proper Noun, excludes preposition before PP
VPItProp -> VPPastIT | VPItProp PP | VP_Aux_It

%Intransitive Verbs in past tense (left, arrived), (arrived quickly), (quickly left)
VPPastIT -> ITVerbPast | ITVerbPast Adv | Adv ITVerbPast

%Intransitive Verbs in gerundive tense
VPGerIT -> ITGer | ITGer Adv | Adv ITGer

%Intransitive present tense verbs
VPPresIT -> ITVerbPres | ITVerbPres Adv | Adv ITVerbPres

%======================VERB PHRASE Transitive (VP_T)===================

%VP for transitives
VP_T -> VPTProp | PP VP_T 

%transitive involving Proper Noun, excludes preposition before PP
VPTProp -> VPPastT | VPTProp PP

%Transitive Verb in paste tense (helped the cat) (brought, told, reminded, gave):
VPPastT -> VPPastMT | VPPastDiT
VPPastMT -> MTVerbPast NP_AllObj | Adv MTVerbPast NP_AllObj | MTVerbPast NP_AllObj Adv
VPPastDiT -> DiTVerbPast NPrp NP_AllObj | DiTVerbPast PosProN NP_AllObj

%Transitive Verbs in gerundive tense (fondling) -> 
VPGerT -> MTGer | MTGer Adv | Adv MTGer | DiTGer | DiTGer Adv | Adv DiTGer

%Transitive present tense verbs (fondle)
VPPresT -> MTVerbPres NP | Adv MTVerbPres NP

%Transitive past tense verbs
TVerbPast -> MTVerbPast | DiTVerbPast

%Transitive present tense verbs
TVerbPres -> MTVerbPres | DiTVerbPres

%Transitive gerund verbs
TGer -> MTGer | DiTGer

%======================Auxilaries===================

VP_Aux_It -> PastPrin | ModPerf | FutProgMod | ProgAux | ProgPastBe | InfV

%Modal Perfect requires only have (could/must have left)
ModPerf -> Modal Perf VPPastIT | Modal Perf ProgBePast VPPastIT

%Prog aux which takes into consideration of present and past (Nadia was leaving)
ProgAux -> Prog VPGerIT | Prog VPPastIT | Prog VPGerT | Prog VPPastT

%Future Progressive Auxilary with modal (will/could/can leave) / (will be leaving)
FutProgMod -> Modal VPPresIT | Modal ProgBe VPGerIT

%Utilization of been/be  (could? has/had/have been leaving)
ProgPastBe -> PerfAll ProgBePast VPGerIT | Modal PerfAll ProgBePast VPGerIT | Modal ProgBe VPPastIT

InfV -> Inf VPPresIT

%Past Principle for intransitive and transitive (existential passive) (have/had/has)
PastPrin -> PerfAll VPPastIT | PerfAll VPPastT


%====================Other===================

%combines has had have
PerfAll -> PerfHH | Perf